Do you sometimes feel completely overwhelmed when life's problems cause you anxiety?

00:01:31.890 --> 00:01:37.890
Just trying to provide the necessities for one's family can lead to anxiety.

00:01:37.890 --> 00:01:43.890
At the same time, you might be dealing with a chronic or life-threatening illness,

00:01:44.890 --> 00:01:54.890
caring for a sick or elderly relative, grieving the death of a loved one, loneliness, a natural disaster,

00:01:54.890 --> 00:02:01.890
or maybe you're struggling with the devastating effects of past or present abuse.

00:02:01.890 --> 00:02:08.889
Now, you firmly believe that God's kingdom will fix these problems, but that's in the future.

00:02:08.889 --> 00:02:11.889
What about today?

00:02:12.889 --> 00:02:16.889
Perhaps you feel like David, who prayed at Psalm 13 and verse 2,

00:02:16.889 --> 00:02:23.889
how long will I have anxious concern with grief in my heart each day?

00:02:23.889 --> 00:02:29.889
A sister who has struggled with anxiety for many years wrote this,

00:02:29.889 --> 00:02:37.889
anxiety robs me of sleep, impacts my health, affects the way I treat others,

00:02:37.889 --> 00:02:41.889
and makes me want to give up. She added,

00:02:41.889 --> 00:02:49.889
anxiety is like a monster that lives in my body somewhere between my heart and my belly.

00:02:49.889 --> 00:02:53.889
I cannot wait for Jehovah to kill that monster in the new world.

00:02:53.889 --> 00:03:00.889
But until then, the monster snarls and tears at my insides and tries to take over my life.

00:03:00.889 --> 00:03:06.139
Can you identify with her feelings?

00:03:06.139 --> 00:03:10.139
We often hear a person say concerning anxiety,

00:03:10.139 --> 00:03:13.139
I'm just trying to take it one day at a time.

00:03:13.139 --> 00:03:16.139
But one brother put it this way.

00:03:16.139 --> 00:03:23.139
I try to take it one day at a time, but sometimes several days attack me at once.

00:03:23.139 --> 00:03:29.139
For so many of us, anxiety is a daily struggle.

00:03:29.139 --> 00:03:34.139
If you battle with anxiety, please know this.

00:03:34.139 --> 00:03:39.139
You are not alone. Do not give up the fight.

00:03:39.139 --> 00:03:47.139
Jehovah and Jesus are aware of the anxieties that weigh on your mind and that are deep in your heart.

00:03:47.139 --> 00:03:54.139
The governing body knows that living in this system of things is especially hard to deal with.

00:03:54.139 --> 00:04:03.379
So the theme chosen for this program is deal with anxiety one day at a time.

00:04:03.379 --> 00:04:06.379
First, what is anxiety?

00:04:06.379 --> 00:04:12.379
In the Christian Greek scriptures, the word anxious occurs 19 times.

00:04:12.379 --> 00:04:16.379
The first occurrence is in Jesus' sermon on the Mount.

00:04:16.379 --> 00:04:20.379
Now Jesus knew that people worried about how to provide for their family.

00:04:20.379 --> 00:04:27.379
So had Matthew, chapter 6, and verse 25, he gave this wise counsel.

00:04:27.379 --> 00:04:36.379
On this account, I say to you, stop being anxious about your life as to what you eat or what you will drink.

00:04:36.379 --> 00:04:39.379
Or about your body as to what you will wear.

00:04:39.379 --> 00:04:44.379
Does not life mean more than food and the body than clothing?

00:04:44.379 --> 00:04:49.949
The study Bible note for verse 25 says,

00:04:49.949 --> 00:04:59.949
the degree term for anxious can refer to worry that divides a person's mind and distracts him, robbing him of joy.

00:04:59.949 --> 00:05:08.949
At Luke 12, verse 29, Jesus says to stop being an anxious suspense or to stop worrying.

00:05:08.949 --> 00:05:17.949
The study note here says that the Greek word for anxious suspense was used to refer to ships being tossed at sea.

00:05:17.949 --> 00:05:30.949
It says that Jesus used it figuratively for being anxious or unsettled as if tossed about or wavering because of doubt and anxiety.

00:05:30.949 --> 00:05:38.949
By saying, stop being anxious, Jesus recognizes that anxiety is already in progress.

00:05:38.949 --> 00:05:42.949
He is very aware of our imperfect nature.

00:05:42.949 --> 00:05:56.949
He knows that we tend to bring our worries from yesterday, the would haves, could haves, and should haves, and our imagined worries about tomorrow, the what ifs to today.

00:05:56.949 --> 00:06:09.949
But ask yourself, how often have I word myself sick about what might happen tomorrow only to find that tomorrow wasn't nearly as bad as I feared it would be?

00:06:09.949 --> 00:06:16.949
Jesus also knows that anxiety can have real, sometimes painful consequences.

00:06:16.949 --> 00:06:20.949
It can stop us from making spiritual progress.

00:06:20.949 --> 00:06:27.949
Over thinking and over analyzing our problems can literally shut us down.

00:06:27.949 --> 00:06:33.949
How though can we stop being anxious? What's the antidote?

00:06:33.949 --> 00:06:37.949
Let's consider four practical things we can do.

00:06:37.949 --> 00:06:44.949
First, rely on Jehovah and take one day at a time.

00:06:44.949 --> 00:06:53.949
This is exactly what Jesus prescribed for us at Matthew chapter 6, verses 33 and 34.

00:06:53.949 --> 00:07:00.949
Keep on then seeking first the kingdom and his righteousness, and all these other things will be added to you.

00:07:01.949 --> 00:07:09.949
So, never be anxious about the next day for the next day will have its own anxieties.

00:07:09.949 --> 00:07:13.949
Each day has enough of its own troubles.

00:07:13.949 --> 00:07:29.949
Verse 34 has a study note telling us that undue anxiety about what may happen in the future can adversely affect a person's relationship with God, causing him to rely on his own wisdom rather than on God's.

00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.949
So what's the lesson?

00:07:31.949 --> 00:07:39.949
Instead of relying on ourselves, rely on Jehovah and take one day at a time.

00:07:39.949 --> 00:07:45.949
A cross reference to Matthew 6, 34 takes us to Exodus 16, verse 4.

00:07:45.949 --> 00:07:54.949
In this account, Jehovah provided the Israelites with enough mana for every day of their 40-year trek.

00:07:54.949 --> 00:07:58.949
Could Jehovah have provided a week's worth of mana?

00:07:58.949 --> 00:08:03.949
A month's worth, a year's worth, of course.

00:08:03.949 --> 00:08:09.949
So why did he only provide enough for each day? Well, think about it.

00:08:09.949 --> 00:08:21.949
When they stepped out of their tents each morning, there was no question whether there would be mana on the ground or not, and there was no question where it came from.

00:08:21.949 --> 00:08:28.949
Jehovah never failed to provide for their needs, not even for one day.

00:08:28.949 --> 00:08:34.950
They also knew from the past that Jehovah always provided for those who were loyal to him.

00:08:34.950 --> 00:08:38.950
We too can look back at how Jehovah provided for his servants.

00:08:38.950 --> 00:08:50.950
We can have complete confidence that Jehovah knows exactly what we need when we need it, for today, tomorrow, and for all eternity.

00:08:51.950 --> 00:08:57.950
Even if we have such confidence, why do we sometimes continue to feel anxious?

00:08:57.950 --> 00:09:05.950
The simple answer, we're imperfect people trying our best to serve Jehovah in Satan's wicked world.

00:09:05.950 --> 00:09:13.950
Daily challenges cause anxiety that can make us forget to rely on Jehovah and take one day at a time.

00:09:13.950 --> 00:09:18.950
So we need to add our second way to deal with anxiety.

00:09:18.950 --> 00:09:22.950
Pour your heart out to Jehovah in earnest prayer.

00:09:22.950 --> 00:09:29.950
Read with me the reassuring words at Philippians 4 verses 6 and 7.

00:09:29.950 --> 00:09:41.950
Do not be anxious over anything, but in everything by prayer and supplication, along with Thanksgiving, let your petitions be made known to God.

00:09:42.950 --> 00:09:52.950
And the peace of God that surpasses all understanding will guard your hearts and your mental powers by means of Christ Jesus.

00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:58.950
Paul doesn't simply tell us not to be anxious, but he tells us how.

00:09:58.950 --> 00:10:06.950
He said by prayer and supplication, which is earnest and specific prayer.

00:10:06.950 --> 00:10:08.950
With what benefit?

00:10:08.950 --> 00:10:13.950
The peace of God will guard your hearts.

00:10:13.950 --> 00:10:19.950
Guard was a military expression referring to troops assigned to protect a city.

00:10:19.950 --> 00:10:25.950
The inhabitants could sleep soundly, knowing that soldiers were guarding them at night.

00:10:25.950 --> 00:10:33.950
In a similar way, when we have the peace of God, our hearts and minds can rest.

00:10:33.950 --> 00:10:38.950
This can prevent us from being overwhelmed by anxiety or discouragement.

00:10:38.950 --> 00:10:45.950
How reassuring are the words of the Psalmist at Psalm 4 and verse 8.

00:10:45.950 --> 00:10:54.950
I will lie down and sleep in peace. For you alone, O Jehovah, make me dwell in security.

00:10:54.950 --> 00:11:06.950
So when we feel trapped, like there's no way out of our worries, the peace from God gives us hope that there's light at the end of the tunnel.

00:11:06.950 --> 00:11:09.950
What though must you do?

00:11:09.950 --> 00:11:14.950
Turn your worries into deep, heartfelt prayers.

00:11:14.950 --> 00:11:23.950
In fact, at 1 Peter 5 and verse 7, Jehovah invites you to throw all your anxiety on him and leave it with him.

00:11:23.950 --> 00:11:26.950
Because he cares for you.

00:11:26.950 --> 00:11:31.950
Jehovah is the one person who truly understands how you feel.

00:11:31.950 --> 00:11:38.950
He knows every moment of your life, why you feel or react a certain way.

00:11:38.950 --> 00:11:48.950
He loves and values you personally, despite your imperfections, your anxieties, your cares and worries.

00:11:48.950 --> 00:11:53.950
He not only has the power to help you, he wants to.

00:11:53.950 --> 00:12:06.950
Knowing this should move you to pray specifically, express in your deepest emotions, and plead that he grant you peace of mind and heart.

00:12:06.950 --> 00:12:14.950
To the extent you do so, 1 Peter 5, 10 promises that he will make you firm.

00:12:14.950 --> 00:12:20.950
He will make you strong. He will firmly ground you.

00:12:20.950 --> 00:12:24.950
Never underestimate the power of prayer.

00:12:24.950 --> 00:12:32.299
Jehovah is always ready to help you one day at a time.

00:12:32.299 --> 00:12:39.299
Our third way to deal with anxiety is to read and meditate on God's Word.

00:12:39.299 --> 00:12:41.299
Let Jehovah speak to you.

00:12:41.299 --> 00:12:46.299
Allow Jehovah's thoughts to become your thoughts.

00:12:46.299 --> 00:12:53.299
At Psalm 94-19, notice how the psalmist admitted his own anxiety.

00:12:54.799 --> 00:13:01.799
When anxieties overwhelmed me, you comforted and soothed me.

00:13:01.799 --> 00:13:11.799
Yes, even servants of God can feel overwhelmed by anxieties, or as one translation says, burden with worries.

00:13:11.799 --> 00:13:17.799
That in itself is comforting, that an inspired Bible writer struggled with anxieties.

00:13:17.799 --> 00:13:25.799
But Jehovah comforted and soothed him, calming his troubled heart.

00:13:25.799 --> 00:13:30.799
God can do the same for us through his inspired word of the Bible.

00:13:30.799 --> 00:13:35.799
Remember, the Bible is how Jehovah speaks to us.

00:13:35.799 --> 00:13:43.799
Rather than allowing our emotions to run wild, we can learn to focus our mind on upbuilding things,

00:13:43.799 --> 00:13:49.799
such as what the Apostle Paul listed at Philippians 4 and verse 8.

00:13:49.799 --> 00:13:56.799
Finally, brothers, whatever things are true, whatever things are of serious concern,

00:13:56.799 --> 00:14:02.799
whatever things are righteous, whatever things are chased, whatever things are lovable,

00:14:02.799 --> 00:14:07.799
whatever things are well spoken of, whatever things are virtuous,

00:14:07.799 --> 00:14:14.799
and whatever things are praiseworthy, continue considering these things.

00:14:14.799 --> 00:14:22.799
The footnote, to verse 8, shows that considering involves thinking about or meditating on.

00:14:22.799 --> 00:14:27.799
We can and should meditate on positive things from the Bible,

00:14:27.799 --> 00:14:33.799
replacing negative things that may enter our mind and cause anxiety.

00:14:33.799 --> 00:14:40.799
Ask Jehovah to help you to find passages in his word that will sooth your heart.

00:14:40.799 --> 00:14:45.799
Ask others what scriptures have calmed their heart during anxious moments.

00:14:45.799 --> 00:14:53.799
Make your own personal list, then set aside time to read and meditate on those passages.

00:14:53.799 --> 00:14:58.799
Meditation is the doorway to your heart.

00:14:58.799 --> 00:15:04.799
Meditation lets God's thoughts affect you on the deepest possible level.

00:15:04.799 --> 00:15:10.799
Imagine that Jehovah is speaking directly to you because he is.

00:15:10.799 --> 00:15:18.799
Never underestimate the power of God's word, of letting Jehovah speak to you.

00:15:18.799 --> 00:15:24.799
Our fourth way to deal with anxiety is to share your feelings with a trusted friend.

00:15:24.799 --> 00:15:30.080
Proverbs 12.25 says,

00:15:30.080 --> 00:15:36.080
anxiety in a man's heart weighs it down, or as a footnote says, depresses him.

00:15:36.080 --> 00:15:39.080
But a good word cheers it up.

00:15:39.080 --> 00:15:47.080
A good word can come from a fellow believer who is motivated by God's spirit and guided by his word.

00:15:47.080 --> 00:15:53.080
When the Apostle Paul was alone in prison, he prayed for encouragement,

00:15:53.080 --> 00:15:57.080
and Jehovah provided what he needed to cheer him up.

00:15:57.080 --> 00:16:02.080
With a heart full of appreciation, he said at Colossians 4.11,

00:16:02.080 --> 00:16:10.080
that my fellow workers have become a source of great comfort to me, or a strengthening aid.

00:16:10.080 --> 00:16:16.080
What can you do if you feel weighed down or imprisoned by anxiety?

00:16:16.080 --> 00:16:19.080
Like Paul, pray for encouragement.

00:16:19.080 --> 00:16:25.080
Pray for someone you can talk to, someone you can trust with your feelings.

00:16:25.080 --> 00:16:31.080
The answer to your prayer may be an elder or a mature Christian brother or sister.

00:16:31.080 --> 00:16:37.080
But what if it's difficult for you to open up to others and confide in them?

00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:43.080
Try the advice in the March 1st, 1997 Watchtower article,

00:16:43.080 --> 00:16:45.080
Are you afraid to trust others?

00:16:45.080 --> 00:16:51.080
When confiding in someone, it says, reveal your concerns gradually.

00:16:51.080 --> 00:16:57.080
If he or she responds in an appropriate, sympathetic, and discrete way,

00:16:57.080 --> 00:17:01.080
you might then try disclosing more.

00:17:01.080 --> 00:17:08.079
Even if it takes some effort, never underestimate the power of our brotherhood.

00:17:08.079 --> 00:17:14.079
Jehovah can use a fellow worshiper to ease your mind of anxious concern.

00:17:14.079 --> 00:17:20.079
Even at times when there's no one to talk to, we can let the experiences,

00:17:20.079 --> 00:17:28.079
like building music and talks on JW broadcasting, be like an encouraging hug from a trusted friend.

00:17:28.079 --> 00:17:34.079
Yes, when we make the effort, we give Jehovah something to bless.

00:17:34.079 --> 00:17:39.079
Jehovah can help us conquer the seemingly incomparable.

00:17:39.079 --> 00:17:46.079
That may not mean that we'll completely eliminate anxiety, but we can learn to take control.

00:17:46.079 --> 00:17:50.079
How? Remember our four ways.

00:17:50.079 --> 00:17:56.079
First, rely on Jehovah and take one day at a time.

00:17:56.079 --> 00:18:02.079
Second, pour out your heart to Jehovah in earnest, specific prayer.

00:18:02.079 --> 00:18:06.079
Third, read and meditate on God's word.

00:18:06.079 --> 00:18:09.079
Let Jehovah speak to you.

00:18:09.079 --> 00:18:13.079
And fourth, share your feelings with a trusted friend.

00:18:13.079 --> 00:18:20.079
With Jehovah's help, you can deal with anxiety one day at a time.

