00:21:57.079 --> 00:22:02.079
So when I come into the refrigerator in the morning, if the magnets are turned, we know where she's at.

00:22:02.079 --> 00:22:04.079
If they're not turned, we know we're in trouble.

00:22:04.079 --> 00:22:05.079
It's a bad day.

00:22:05.079 --> 00:22:06.079
Time to do something else.

00:22:07.079 --> 00:22:12.079
So what can others do or say that would be helpful to those going through anxiety?

00:22:12.079 --> 00:22:21.079
For the friends, it's really nice when they're understanding and non-judgmental and respect my privacy.

00:22:21.079 --> 00:22:22.079
That's really helpful.

00:22:22.079 --> 00:22:29.079
And when they don't freeze me in time, decide that, oh, she's anxious and this is how she's going to be all the time.

00:22:29.079 --> 00:22:31.079
That's really helpful.

00:22:31.079 --> 00:22:34.079
I even forget that Jehovah approves of me.

00:22:34.079 --> 00:22:41.079
So reminding me of that, reminding me that the things that I do to please him are successful.

00:22:41.079 --> 00:22:46.079
And maybe even reminding me of things that I've accomplished for Jehovah in the past.

